body:
> obrakmann Is that what you wanted?

Not quite. I'd like `abortMissionButton.OnClick` to look like this:

``` csharp
            abortMissionButton.OnClick = () =>
            {
                hideMenu = true;
                Action restartAction = null;
                if (world.IsReplay || world.Map.Visibility == MapVisibility.MissionSelector)
                {
                    var iop = world.WorldActor.TraitsImplementing<IObjectivesPanel>().FirstOrDefault();
                    var exitDelay = iop != null ? iop.ExitDelay : 0;
                    restartAction = () =>
                    {
                        Ui.CloseWindow();
                        if (mpe != null)
                        {
                            if (Game.IsCurrentWorld(world))
                                mpe.Fade(MenuPaletteEffect.EffectType.Black);
                            exitDelay += 40 * mpe.Info.FadeLength;
                        }

                        Game.RunAfterDelay(exitDelay, () =>
                        {
                            Game.RestartGame();
                        });
                    };
                }

                if (world.LocalPlayer == null || world.LocalPlayer.WinState != WinState.Won &&
                    (!world.IsGameOver || world.Map.Visibility == MapVisibility.MissionSelector))
                {
                    ConfirmationDialogs.PromptConfirmAction(
                        title: "Leave Mission",
                        text: "Leave this game and return to the menu?",
                        onConfirm: onQuit,
                        onCancel: showMenu,
                        confirmText: "Leave",
                        cancelText: "Stay",
                        otherText: "Restart",
                        onOther: restartAction);
                }
                else
                    onQuit();
            };
```

That will result in the following behaviour:
- Any game, in progress => Show prompt
- Skirmish game, when game is over => Don't show prompt
- Mission, when game is over
  - if the player won => Don't show prompt
  - if the player lost => Show prompt
